  "texts": [
    "This viewpoint is reinforced by the performance of [119].",
    "Whilst their incorporation of geometric relationships into the Transformer attention model works well, it falls short of the performance of models that specifically use a spatial graph [87,89,115].",
    "These results show that if a specific relationship, one that can be expressed explicitly as a graph, is being exploited by a model, then its architecture should make use of a GNN to take advantage of the graph.",
    "The spatial relationships between objects form a graph, and therefore, a GNN is well suited to make use of this information.Although Transformers can be viewed as operating on a complete graph and pruning edges via the attention mechanism [41], we have demonstrated in this survey that this is not always the best approach.",
    "This raises the questions of 1) which graph should be used?"
  ]
}